<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06187</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTIONS 236 AND 237 (A), (B), OF CHAPTER IV, TITLE I, BOOK II, OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 7160, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT CODE OF 1991</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to impose additional Ad Valorem tax on idle lands at the rate of five percent (5%) intended to disincentivized  the owners whose lands, many remained undeveloped, much less utilized.

Provides for the coverage of idle lands, and those that should NOT be considered idle as follows:

a) Agricultural lands planted WITH VEGETABLE OR FRUIT BEARING CROPS OR with at least TWO HUNDRED (200)
trees to a hectare, OR A PROPORTIONATE NUMBER OF TREES IF SUCH LAND IS EITHER LESS THAN OR MORE THAN ONE HECTARE; and

b) LANDS PLANTED WITH AT LEAST ONE (1) TREE FOR EVERY FIFTY (50) SQUARE METERS, OR AT LEAST FIFTY PERCENT (50%) OF THE AREA IS PLANTED WITH VEGETABLE OR FRUIT BEARING CROPS FOR A PERIOD OF AT LEAST SIX (6) MONTHS IN A YEAR.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALO, RON P.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-05</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LOCAL GOVERNMENT ON 2020-02-10</td></tr></table>